<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4042] TestDistributedLogSplitting broke on trunk</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4042</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a couple of issues going on here.  Its taken me a while to figure whats up and am still not done.  Here&apos;s what I found so far:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+ The last test testWorkerAbort has been hanging because there is no one to process the log split the final assert is expecting completed; we&apos;ve killed the lone RS that this test put up.  This test passes most of the time for me locally; luck has the log processed before the RS with its splitLogWorker processes the log before we go out.  Putting up a new RS with a splitLogWorker makes this test pass for me most of the time now but I&apos;ve seen an error in testing so need to dig in still.&lt;br/&gt;
+ The first test, testThreeRSAbort is a good test.  Its turning up a issue that has nothing to do w/ log splitting.  If .META. is on one of the RSs that goes down &amp;#8211; we launch w/ 6 RSs &amp;#8211; then we get stuck in catalog tracker waiting on meta to be up again (though it deploys fin &amp;#8211; we don&apos;t notice its deploy in master).  I&apos;m on this one at mo. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
